The defendant CARISSA B BIESENTHAL was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

2:44 PM Defendant CARISSA B BIESENTHAL in court.  Attorney Gerise Marie Laspisa in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Justin M Sondalle in court for CARISSA B BIESENTHAL. DA recites agreement - will amend to misdemeanor obstructing with costs and DNA sample. DA moves to amend count 1 of the information to Obstructing in violation of 946.41(1). Atty Sondalle concurs. Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant. Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights. Court goes over the elements of each offense. Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty. Court instructs defendant regarding deportation. (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions. 

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST. Court finds the plea is made knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently. Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea. Court finds the defendant guilty on the amended count 1. Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today. Nothing further on Sentencing by DA. Sentencing statement by Atty Sondalle. No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

-Court costs and DNA sample - $443.00. Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or call the Clerk of Courts Office (920-294-4142) to set-up a payment plan. 
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.
